dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 315 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 51.0000. South Decimal Degree 50.8333. East Decimal Degree -1.2667. West Decimal Degree -1.6667. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological survey on the one-inch scale by H. W. Bristow, F.R.S. published on Sheet 11 and 15, Old Series, 1856 and 1858. Resurveyed on the six-inch scale by W. Whitaker et al. Published with Drift Aug 1899.".
dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Southampton, drift, sheet 315
